quran[35]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,Successful indeed are the believers
  23,2,Those who are humble during their worship (salat)
  23,3,and those who keep away from what is vain
  23,4,and those who are active in giving charity (zakat)
  23,5,and those who guard their private parts
  23,6,"except from their mates or those whom their right hands possess, then (in their case) they are certainly free of blame"
  23,7,"but whoever seeks beyond that, then those are the persons who transgress"
  23,8,and those who are keepers of their trusts and their agreements
  23,9,and those who guard their worship (salat)
  23,10,Those are the inheritors
  23,11,"who will inherit paradise, they will stay in it"
  23,12,And We have indeed created man from something taken out from clay
  23,13,Then We made it a sperm in a settling place
  23,14,"then We proportioned the sperm (into) that which clings and hangs like a leech, then We proportioned that which clings and hangs like a leech (into a thing like) chewed flesh, then We proportioned (the thing like) chewed flesh (into) bones, then We clothed the bones with flesh, then We developed him in another creation. So blessed be God, the Best of Proportioners"
  23,15,Then after that you certainly die
  23,16,Then on the day of resurrection you will certainly be raised
  23,17,"And We have created seven paths above you, and We are not heedless of the creation"
  23,18,"And We send down water from the sky with a (set) programme, then We settle it in the earth, and We have the power on its removal"
  23,19,"And from it We produce gardens of date palms and grapes for you, there are many fruits for you in them and you eat from them"
  23,20,"and the (olive) tree that springs out from Mount Sinai, growing with oil (in it) and a curry for those who eat"
  23,21,"And there is certainly a lesson for you in the cattle, We make you to drink from that which is in their stomachs and there are many benefits for you in them and (some) of them you eat"
  23,22,and on them and on the ships you are carried. (R)
  23,23,"And We had sent Noah to his people so he said, \"O my people! serve (worship) God, there is no god for you other than Him. Will you not then guard (against the evil of worshipping others)"
  23,24,"So the leaders of those who did not believe from among his people said, \"He is no more than a man like yourselves, he intends to achieve superiority over you, and had God willed He would have sent down angels, We have not heard this among our ancient forefathers"
  23,25,"He is nothing but a man who is possessed by jinn, so bear with him till (some) time"
  23,26,"He said, \"My Lord! help me because they deny me"
  23,27,"So We communicated to him, \"Make the ship before Our eyes and (according to) Our communication. Then when Our commandment comes and the water gushes forth from (the reservoir in) the valley, make each pair (consisting) of two, to enter the (ship) along with your people, except him among them against whom the word has already gone forth, and do not speak to me regarding those who are unjust, they will certainly be drowned"
  23,28,"Then when you are balanced on the ship, you and those with you, then say: \"Praise is due only for God Who delivered us from the unjust people"
  23,29,"And say, \"My Lord! make me alight a blessed alighting and You are the Best of those who cause to alight"
  23,30,"There are certainly signs in that, and We are ever testing (people)"
  23,31,Then after them We produced another generation
  23,32,"then We sent among them a messenger from among themselves (saying), \"Serve God, there is no god for you other than Him. Will you not then guard (against the evil of worshipping others)"
  23,33,"And the leaders of his people who did not believe and denied the meeting of the hereafter and whom We had made to enjoy in the life of the world said, “This is no more than a man like yourselves, he eats from that from which you eat and he drinks from that which you drink"
  23,34,"And if you obey a man like yourselves, then you will certainly be of the losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you, that when you are dead and you become (part of the) soil and bones, that you will be brought out (alive again)"